API Documentation

Overview
This document describes the endpoints, request parameters, and responses for the custom user registration, authentication, and search functionality for a Django application.

Endpoints

Student Registration
URL: /api/student/register/
Method: POST
Description: Registers a new student user and saves personal, college, course, and work experience data.

Request Body:

json
{
  "student": {
    "username": "student_username",
    "password": "student_password"
  },
  "data": {
    "name": "John Doe",
    "Gender": "Male",
    "DOB": "1990-01-01",
    "Contact_no": 1234567890,
    "Whatsapp_no": 9876543210,
    "Qualification": "Bachelor's",
    "college": "XYZ University",
    "course": "Computer Science",
    "company": "ABC Corp",
    "role": "Software Engineer"
  }
}
Response:

json
{
  "status": 1
}
Or in case of error:

json
{
  "status": 0
}




User Login
URL: /api/login/
Method: POST
Description: Authenticates a user and returns a JWT token upon successful authentication.

Request Body:

json

{
  "username": "student_username",
  "password": "student_password"
}
Response:

json

{
  "token": [
    {
      "token": "jwt_token"
    }
  ],
  "status": [
    {
      "status": 1
    }
  ]
}
Or in case of error:

json

[
  {
    "status": 0
  }
]




Student Detail
URL: /api/studentdetails/
Method: GET
Description: Retrieves details of the logged-in student. Accessible only to admin users.

Headers:

Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>
Response:

json

{
  "user": {
    "id": 1,
    "username": "admin"
  },
  "personal": {
    "enquiry_no": 1,
    "enquiry_date": "2023-01-01",
    "Name": "John Doe",
    "Gender": "Male",
    "DOB": "1990-01-01",
    "Contact_no": 1234567890,
    "Whatsapp_no": 9876543210,
    "Qualification": "Bachelor's"
  },
  "college": [
    {
      "college": "XYZ University"
    }
  ],
  "course": [
    {
      "course": "Computer Science"
    }
  ],
  "work_experience": [
    {
      "company": "ABC Corp",
      "role": "Software Engineer"
    }
  ]
}



User Search
URL: /admin/search/
Method: GET
Description: Searches users based on provided query parameters. Accessible only to admin users.

Headers:

Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>
Query Parameters:

enquiry_no (optional): Integer
name (optional): String
gender (optional): String
qualification (optional): String
college (optional): String
contact_number (optional): Integer
whatsapp_number (optional): Integer
dob (optional): Date (YYYY-MM-DD)
work_experience (optional): String
Response:

json

[
  {
    "personal": {
      "enquiry_no": 1,
      "enquiry_date": "2023-01-01",
      "Name": "John Doe",
      "Gender": "Male",
      "DOB": "1990-01-01",
      "Contact_no": 1234567890,
      "Whatsapp_no": 9876543210,
      "Qualification": "Bachelor's"
    },
    "college": [
      {
        "college": "XYZ University"
      }
    ],
    "course": [
      {
        "course": "Computer Science"
      }
    ],
    "work_experience": [
      {
        "company": "ABC Corp",
        "role": "Software Engineer"
      }
    ]
  }
]
